---
/**
 * "Why This Catalog Exists" section. Relies on shared section styles
 * from about.astro.
 */
import { SPRINGER_PAPER_URL, THESIS_URL } from '../../lib/constants';
---

<div class="about-section reveal-left" id="sec-origin">
  <div class="section-label">Origin</div>
  <h2>Why This Catalog Exists</h2>

  <p>
    I spent the better part of a year reading every academic paper I could find on code smells. What
    I found was frustrating:
  </p>

  <ul class="origin-struck">
    <li>
      <span class="origin-struck__text">
        <strong>Papers</strong> buried them in academic prose nobody had time to parse.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="origin-struck__text">
        <strong>Books</strong> scattered them across chapters with no unified view.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="origin-struck__text">
        <strong>Blog posts</strong> covered the same handful &mdash; always Long Method, always God Class.
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="origin-verdict">Nowhere had all of them in one place.</p>

  <p class="origin-pivot">So I built one.</p>

  <p>
    I turned it into my <a href={THESIS_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener"
      ><strong>Master&rsquo;s thesis</strong></a
    > at Wroclaw University of Science and Technology, published alongside a <a
      href={SPRINGER_PAPER_URL}
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener"><strong>Springer Nature research paper</strong></a
    >. One goal:
    <em class="origin-goal">read everything, classify everything, and make it all browsable.</em>
  </p>

  <p>
    Every entry has a paper trail. Who named it, when, where. Which smells it causes and which cause
    it. What it breaks, and how to fix it.
  </p>

  <p class="origin-bridge">
    What I wished existed &mdash; five ways to look at every smell, and a map of how they&rsquo;re
    all connected.
  </p>
</div>

<style>
  /* Struck manuscript — each frustration has a hand-drawn strikethrough */
  .origin-struck {
    margin: 24px 0 20px;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .origin-struck li {
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 18px;
  }

  .origin-struck li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 11px;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    opacity: 0.45;
  }

  .origin-struck__text {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    position: relative;
    display: inline;
  }

  .origin-struck__text::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: -2px;
    right: -2px;
    top: 52%;
    height: 1.5px;
    background: var(--accent);
    opacity: 0.45;
    transform: rotate(-0.4deg);
    border-radius: 1px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .origin-struck li:nth-child(2) .origin-struck__text::after {
    transform: rotate(0.3deg);
    top: 54%;
  }

  .origin-struck li:nth-child(3) .origin-struck__text::after {
    transform: rotate(-0.2deg);
    top: 50%;
  }

  .origin-struck :global(strong) {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Verdict — quiet, factual */
  .origin-verdict {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    margin-top: -4px;
  }

  /* Pivot — the turn; clean, no strikethrough, accent color */
  .origin-pivot {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 28;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  /* Inline links — match article-prose pattern */
  #sec-origin a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 30%, transparent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition:
      color var(--duration-fast),
      text-decoration-color var(--duration-fast);
  }

  #sec-origin a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  /* Goal — subtle inline emphasis */
  .origin-goal {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Bridge — earned silence via whitespace, then display italic */
  .origin-bridge {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 350;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 40px;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  :global(html[data-motion='reduced']) .origin-struck__text::after {
    transform: none;
  }
</style>
